WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.928 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:01.928 --> 00:00:05.302 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.302 --> 00:00:10.122 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:10.122 --> 00:00:13.040 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.040 --> 00:00:18.100 align:middle line:10%
>> When I was around 25, I
discovered this place called

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:20.260 align:middle line:10%
Damanhur.

00:00:20.260 --> 00:00:21.250 align:middle line:10%
I thought, OK.

00:00:21.250 --> 00:00:24.160 align:middle line:10%
Now I understand where all of
the crazy people like me are.

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:26.740 align:middle line:90%


00:00:26.740 --> 00:00:31.510 align:middle line:84%
>> It's beyond any
words that we could say.

00:00:31.510 --> 00:00:35.150 align:middle line:84%
It gives me the goosebumps
to even think about it.

00:00:35.150 --> 00:00:38.090 align:middle line:10%
It's so important.

00:00:38.090 --> 00:00:40.510 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:00:40.510 --> 00:00:44.230 align:middle line:90%


00:00:44.230 --> 00:00:49.780 align:middle line:84%
>> There was something going on
there that was beyond any words

00:00:49.780 --> 00:00:51.820 align:middle line:90%
that I could possibly explain.

00:00:51.820 --> 00:00:55.045 align:middle line:90%
And it was--

00:00:55.045 --> 00:00:57.215 align:middle line:84%
[SIGH] it was like I
could breathe again.

00:00:57.215 --> 00:01:00.710 align:middle line:90%


00:01:00.710 --> 00:01:05.360 align:middle line:84%
In the early 1970s,
a group of people

00:01:05.360 --> 00:01:09.560 align:middle line:84%
came together in Northern
Italy in total secrecy

00:01:09.560 --> 00:01:13.160 align:middle line:90%
to start creating the temples.

00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:16.850 align:middle line:84%
>> What's amazing about Damanhur
is it's formed this group.

00:01:16.850 --> 00:01:18.530 align:middle line:90%
They're actually a community.

00:01:18.530 --> 00:01:19.550 align:middle line:90%
They've been living it.

00:01:19.550 --> 00:01:22.400 align:middle line:90%


00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:25.070 align:middle line:84%
>> We really believe that it's
possible to unlock the whole

00:01:25.070 --> 00:01:26.030 align:middle line:90%
human potential.

00:01:26.030 --> 00:01:29.210 align:middle line:90%


00:01:29.210 --> 00:01:32.570 align:middle line:84%
>> In Damanhur, we believe
that there are multiple lines

00:01:32.570 --> 00:01:33.850 align:middle line:90%
of reality.

00:01:33.850 --> 00:01:37.310 align:middle line:84%
And so imagine that one
of these lines of reality

00:01:37.310 --> 00:01:40.610 align:middle line:84%
has led humanity to
destroy our planet,

00:01:40.610 --> 00:01:42.455 align:middle line:84%
has led us to a
point of no return.

00:01:42.455 --> 00:01:46.670 align:middle line:90%


00:01:46.670 --> 00:01:52.070 align:middle line:10%
>> It was important for us to
make something solid, visible,

00:01:52.070 --> 00:01:53.840 align:middle line:10%
touchable.

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:58.460 align:middle line:10%
Because otherwise,
it's only theoretical.

00:01:58.460 --> 00:01:59.690 align:middle line:10%
We built the temple.

00:01:59.690 --> 00:02:00.980 align:middle line:10%
We have the community.

00:02:00.980 --> 00:02:04.040 align:middle line:10%
We have people living
there, doing magic

00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:05.990 align:middle line:10%
in their daily life.

00:02:05.990 --> 00:02:06.790 align:middle line:90%
It's possible.

00:02:06.790 --> 00:02:12.290 align:middle line:90%


00:02:12.290 --> 00:02:16.220 align:middle line:84%
>> We believe that we can create
a new branch in time whereby

00:02:16.220 --> 00:02:20.355 align:middle line:84%
events will go differently and
we will not destroy ourselves

00:02:20.355 --> 00:02:21.155 align:middle line:90%
and the planet.

00:02:21.155 --> 00:02:38.100 align:middle line:90%


00:02:38.100 --> 00:02:42.040 align:middle line:90%
[CHILDREN PLAYING]

00:02:42.040 --> 00:02:46.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Damanhur is a federation
of spiritual communities with

00:02:46.030 --> 00:02:50.470 align:middle line:84%
about 600 residing
citizens in Northern Italy.

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:54.010 align:middle line:10%
And all together, about
1,200 with those residing

00:02:54.010 --> 00:02:56.840 align:middle line:10%
all around the world.

00:02:56.840 --> 00:02:59.980 align:middle line:84%
We have our own governing
system, an internal schooling

00:02:59.980 --> 00:03:04.090 align:middle line:84%
system, an alternative currency
system, a daily newspaper,

00:03:04.090 --> 00:03:06.340 align:middle line:90%
and a health care system.

00:03:06.340 --> 00:03:08.980 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:03:08.980 --> 00:03:15.600 align:middle line:90%


00:03:15.600 --> 00:03:19.870 align:middle line:84%
>> The fact that we have in
over 40 years created such

00:03:19.870 --> 00:03:24.610 align:middle line:84%
a physical, tangible reality,
all these very concrete,

00:03:24.610 --> 00:03:27.970 align:middle line:84%
practical, and yet for
us spiritual and magical

00:03:27.970 --> 00:03:29.720 align:middle line:90%
realities.

00:03:29.720 --> 00:03:32.810 align:middle line:10%
>> Damanhur was created
to create an anomaly,

00:03:32.810 --> 00:03:35.060 align:middle line:10%
an anomaly in time.

00:03:35.060 --> 00:03:40.210 align:middle line:84%
We believe that somehow we
are living on a new timeline.

00:03:40.210 --> 00:03:42.190 align:middle line:84%
There are many ways
to tell a story,

00:03:42.190 --> 00:03:44.590 align:middle line:84%
and the story of
Damanhur can be looked

00:03:44.590 --> 00:03:46.465 align:middle line:90%
at from many different angles.

00:03:46.465 --> 00:03:50.280 align:middle line:90%


00:03:50.280 --> 00:03:52.610 align:middle line:84%
So we chose to use the
form of a comic book

00:03:52.610 --> 00:03:58.400 align:middle line:84%
to tell a little more
of a sci-fi story,

00:03:58.400 --> 00:04:00.185 align:middle line:90%
like a cosmic chess.

00:04:00.185 --> 00:04:04.458 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:04.458 --> 00:04:06.913 align:middle line:90%


00:04:06.913 --> 00:04:11.332 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:04:11.332 --> 00:04:25.571 align:middle line:90%


00:04:25.571 --> 00:04:28.070 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:04:28.070 --> 00:04:35.870 align:middle line:90%


00:04:35.870 --> 00:04:39.080 align:middle line:84%
>> The story of Falco
is a complex story,

00:04:39.080 --> 00:04:43.310 align:middle line:84%
and has parts and episodes of
his life that sounds really

00:04:43.310 --> 00:04:45.030 align:middle line:90%
unbelievable.

00:04:45.030 --> 00:04:47.910 align:middle line:84%
One of these episodes
is when he was a child,

00:04:47.910 --> 00:04:51.030 align:middle line:84%
this old man came
knocking on his door

00:04:51.030 --> 00:04:53.680 align:middle line:84%
and left a chest full
of books for him.

00:04:53.680 --> 00:04:57.030 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, Falco
himself from his past

00:04:57.030 --> 00:05:01.110 align:middle line:84%
had come to give
to this Falco boy

00:05:01.110 --> 00:05:04.350 align:middle line:84%
so that he could read
them again and reacquire

00:05:04.350 --> 00:05:06.165 align:middle line:84%
all of his knowledge
and his memories.

00:05:06.165 --> 00:05:09.110 align:middle line:90%


00:05:09.110 --> 00:05:12.170 align:middle line:84%
As soon as young Falco
was reading the page,

00:05:12.170 --> 00:05:15.920 align:middle line:84%
all the writing would disappear,
because this book was not

00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:17.300 align:middle line:90%
a book to be studied.

00:05:17.300 --> 00:05:21.230 align:middle line:84%
It was a book to
reawaken memories.

00:05:21.230 --> 00:05:24.950 align:middle line:84%
So Falco started to become
aware of his vision very young.

00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:28.350 align:middle line:10%
And on his path of growth
and constant research,

00:05:28.350 --> 00:05:31.310 align:middle line:10%
he started to awaken
many abilities.

00:05:31.310 --> 00:05:34.010 align:middle line:10%
>> The things that he was able
to do certainly showed that he

00:05:34.010 --> 00:05:38.270 align:middle line:10%
had capabilities beyond
what most humans can't do.

00:05:38.270 --> 00:05:40.280 align:middle line:84%
>> For instance,
the ability to heal,

00:05:40.280 --> 00:05:43.910 align:middle line:84%
the ability to astral travel,
to retrieve information that was

00:05:43.910 --> 00:05:44.990 align:middle line:90%
necessary.

00:05:44.990 --> 00:05:48.050 align:middle line:84%
And most of all, the
ability to connect

00:05:48.050 --> 00:05:51.320 align:middle line:84%
to higher and higher
forces that showed him

00:05:51.320 --> 00:05:55.070 align:middle line:84%
the possibility of creating
a community and temples

00:05:55.070 --> 00:05:58.370 align:middle line:84%
so that a new line
of time could start.

00:05:58.370 --> 00:06:01.580 align:middle line:84%
Not just, of course, for him
or Damanhur, but for the whole

00:06:01.580 --> 00:06:03.470 align:middle line:90%
of humanity.

00:06:03.470 --> 00:06:06.110 align:middle line:84%
In his early 20s,
Falco decided that it

00:06:06.110 --> 00:06:09.510 align:middle line:84%
was time to find other
people to join forces,

00:06:09.510 --> 00:06:12.690 align:middle line:84%
and so he started to give
his first conferences.

00:06:12.690 --> 00:06:18.170 align:middle line:84%
And at that time, the paranormal
was a theme of great interest

00:06:18.170 --> 00:06:20.390 align:middle line:84%
because we are talking
about the '70s.

00:06:20.390 --> 00:06:23.210 align:middle line:84%
And so he was showing
paranormal stuff

00:06:23.210 --> 00:06:26.510 align:middle line:84%
to get the attention of people,
but his dream and vision

00:06:26.510 --> 00:06:28.180 align:middle line:84%
were not about
being paranormals,

00:06:28.180 --> 00:06:29.750 align:middle line:90%
were about awakening.

00:06:29.750 --> 00:06:32.480 align:middle line:90%


00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:34.610 align:middle line:10%
>> I was born in Florence.

00:06:34.610 --> 00:06:37.130 align:middle line:10%
And when I was 21, I
was very independent.

00:06:37.130 --> 00:06:42.440 align:middle line:84%
I was having my house, my moto,
my books, my music, my work.

00:06:42.440 --> 00:06:45.440 align:middle line:84%
I was quite happy,
but I was feeling

00:06:45.440 --> 00:06:47.610 align:middle line:90%
that I was missing something.

00:06:47.610 --> 00:06:50.750 align:middle line:84%
I discovered Damanhur
in a TV show.

00:06:50.750 --> 00:06:53.870 align:middle line:84%
And in this TV show,
there were these people.

00:06:53.870 --> 00:06:58.310 align:middle line:84%
There were so smiling,
enthusiastic, full of--

00:06:58.310 --> 00:07:00.080 align:middle line:84%
you know, very
convinced they could

00:07:00.080 --> 00:07:02.600 align:middle line:84%
have created this
new society based

00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:06.800 align:middle line:84%
on their dreams and
values, and nothing

00:07:06.800 --> 00:07:07.800 align:middle line:90%
could have stopped them.

00:07:07.800 --> 00:07:08.780 align:middle line:90%
And I say, oh my god.

00:07:08.780 --> 00:07:10.160 align:middle line:90%
This is interesting.

00:07:10.160 --> 00:07:12.230 align:middle line:90%
I have to go and see.

00:07:12.230 --> 00:07:13.470 align:middle line:90%
So I did.

00:07:13.470 --> 00:07:17.720 align:middle line:84%
And when I came here, I have
to see, these crazy people,

00:07:17.720 --> 00:07:18.830 align:middle line:90%
because they were crazy.

00:07:18.830 --> 00:07:21.275 align:middle line:84%
And I still think
we are quite crazy.

00:07:21.275 --> 00:07:26.210 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] You know, they
really take my heart.

00:07:26.210 --> 00:07:30.270 align:middle line:84%
I was so touched by their
smile, their energy,

00:07:30.270 --> 00:07:33.920 align:middle line:84%
their enthusiasm of leading,
of creating something new.

00:07:33.920 --> 00:07:37.250 align:middle line:84%
A big, huge dream that
could seem impossible,

00:07:37.250 --> 00:07:38.660 align:middle line:90%
and it was not.

00:07:38.660 --> 00:07:42.800 align:middle line:84%
So I decided to be
part of this dream.

00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:45.620 align:middle line:84%
>> In Damanhur, it was said
that there's no such a thing

00:07:45.620 --> 00:07:47.870 align:middle line:90%
as individual enlightenment.

00:07:47.870 --> 00:07:50.990 align:middle line:84%
In order to really
create an alternative,

00:07:50.990 --> 00:07:54.860 align:middle line:84%
you need a system, a society
in which can have education,

00:07:54.860 --> 00:07:58.190 align:middle line:84%
you can have a different
way of eating, different way

00:07:58.190 --> 00:08:01.730 align:middle line:84%
of relating, literally
manifesting a different way

00:08:01.730 --> 00:08:03.500 align:middle line:90%
of life all together.

00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:07.280 align:middle line:10%
Instead of living
like in the cities,

00:08:07.280 --> 00:08:09.710 align:middle line:10%
each person separate with
their own little apartment

00:08:09.710 --> 00:08:13.370 align:middle line:10%
in a little box, and
that sense of separation,

00:08:13.370 --> 00:08:19.460 align:middle line:10%
we value the sense of community
as a way of reawakening

00:08:19.460 --> 00:08:25.340 align:middle line:10%
the natural drive that humans
have of being together simply.

00:08:25.340 --> 00:08:30.050 align:middle line:84%
And this was actually normal
till some decades ago.

00:08:30.050 --> 00:08:33.770 align:middle line:84%
Now in Damanhur, we try
to value solidarity.

00:08:33.770 --> 00:08:36.650 align:middle line:90%


00:08:36.650 --> 00:08:39.929 align:middle line:84%
>> Damanhur is a
federation of communities.

00:08:39.929 --> 00:08:43.370 align:middle line:84%
We believe that human groups
cannot be larger than 200,

00:08:43.370 --> 00:08:47.900 align:middle line:84%
220 people to be able to
maintain that individual

00:08:47.900 --> 00:08:49.350 align:middle line:90%
connection that is real.

00:08:49.350 --> 00:08:52.160 align:middle line:84%
So every time we have a
larger number than this,

00:08:52.160 --> 00:08:53.610 align:middle line:90%
we create a new community.

00:08:53.610 --> 00:08:55.408 align:middle line:90%
[ENERGETIC MUSIC]

00:08:55.408 --> 00:09:00.368 align:middle line:10%
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

00:09:00.368 --> 00:09:01.360 align:middle line:90%


00:09:01.360 --> 00:09:03.850 align:middle line:84%
They live in these
houses called nucleos.

00:09:03.850 --> 00:09:05.808 align:middle line:84%
So there might be 20
people in a house.

00:09:05.808 --> 00:09:07.600 align:middle line:84%
Different families are
the different people

00:09:07.600 --> 00:09:09.183 align:middle line:84%
who have their
separate living spaces,

00:09:09.183 --> 00:09:10.390 align:middle line:90%
but they share a community.

00:09:10.390 --> 00:09:11.530 align:middle line:90%
They share the dining room.

00:09:11.530 --> 00:09:12.330 align:middle line:90%
They eat together.

00:09:12.330 --> 00:09:13.310 align:middle line:90%
They share the kitchen.

00:09:13.310 --> 00:09:14.110 align:middle line:90%
They cook together.

00:09:14.110 --> 00:09:15.840 align:middle line:90%
They share the duties.

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:18.685 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:09:18.685 --> 00:09:36.970 align:middle line:90%


00:09:36.970 --> 00:09:39.160 align:middle line:10%
>> Definitely, my concept
of family is a little bit

00:09:39.160 --> 00:09:40.780 align:middle line:10%
different from the normal one.

00:09:40.780 --> 00:09:43.870 align:middle line:84%
I was born in one
of Damanhur nucleos.

00:09:43.870 --> 00:09:47.350 align:middle line:84%
So I remember growing with
a lot of aunts and uncles

00:09:47.350 --> 00:09:50.170 align:middle line:84%
that still today are
very close to me.

00:09:50.170 --> 00:09:52.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Although the parents are
always the main reference

00:09:52.720 --> 00:09:56.680 align:middle line:84%
point, all the adults of the
community feel responsible with

00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:59.230 align:middle line:84%
their example, the
way they behave,

00:09:59.230 --> 00:10:01.340 align:middle line:90%
for the education of each child.

00:10:01.340 --> 00:10:04.180 align:middle line:84%
We also share
financially the support

00:10:04.180 --> 00:10:06.010 align:middle line:84%
of all the children
of a community.

00:10:06.010 --> 00:10:10.360 align:middle line:84%
We try to give them the
most love and the most

00:10:10.360 --> 00:10:13.060 align:middle line:84%
mind-opening education
they can have.

00:10:13.060 --> 00:10:16.510 align:middle line:84%
>> It helped me a lot in
growing up to have a huge sense

00:10:16.510 --> 00:10:19.810 align:middle line:84%
of empathy, and very able to
understand the differences

00:10:19.810 --> 00:10:21.610 align:middle line:90%
between people.

00:10:21.610 --> 00:10:23.980 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:10:23.980 --> 00:10:32.570 align:middle line:90%


00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:34.880 align:middle line:84%
>> And what is really
important in our schools,

00:10:34.880 --> 00:10:38.910 align:middle line:84%
we teach to our children
to know themselves.

00:10:38.910 --> 00:10:42.600 align:middle line:10%
And when I-- why we think this
is the very important aspect,

00:10:42.600 --> 00:10:45.350 align:middle line:10%
because if you know yourselves,
you know its potential,

00:10:45.350 --> 00:10:48.740 align:middle line:10%
and you get in touch with the
spiritual side of ourselves.

00:10:48.740 --> 00:10:56.640 align:middle line:90%


00:10:56.640 --> 00:11:00.030 align:middle line:84%
In Damanhur, everybody
can choose a name, a plant

00:11:00.030 --> 00:11:01.710 align:middle line:90%
and an animal name.

00:11:01.710 --> 00:11:04.560 align:middle line:84%
>> My name is Baris, and
that means snow leopard

00:11:04.560 --> 00:11:06.210 align:middle line:90%
in the Kazakh language.

00:11:06.210 --> 00:11:09.930 align:middle line:84%
On my passport, my official
name is Setna Bernini.

00:11:09.930 --> 00:11:11.490 align:middle line:90%
Very Italian surname.

00:11:11.490 --> 00:11:14.530 align:middle line:84%
I took my animal
name four years ago.

00:11:14.530 --> 00:11:17.220 align:middle line:84%
And this is a very
important process for us.

00:11:17.220 --> 00:11:19.830 align:middle line:84%
It's part of our
cultural core tradition.

00:11:19.830 --> 00:11:23.280 align:middle line:84%
And it's a name
that you can choose,

00:11:23.280 --> 00:11:25.740 align:middle line:84%
but you cannot
assign to yourself.

00:11:25.740 --> 00:11:27.825 align:middle line:90%
It's a collective process.

00:11:27.825 --> 00:11:30.450 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:11:30.450 --> 00:11:33.570 align:middle line:90%


00:11:33.570 --> 00:11:36.030 align:middle line:84%
>> You get in one of their
general meetings and you ask

00:11:36.030 --> 00:11:37.560 align:middle line:90%
for your name.

00:11:37.560 --> 00:11:39.810 align:middle line:90%
And many things can happen.

00:11:39.810 --> 00:11:42.441 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:11:42.441 --> 00:11:46.290 align:middle line:90%
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

00:11:46.290 --> 00:11:48.300 align:middle line:84%
>> People can make
another suggestion.

00:11:48.300 --> 00:11:51.025 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:11:51.025 --> 00:11:54.350 align:middle line:10%
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

00:11:54.350 --> 00:11:55.840 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:58.660 align:middle line:84%
>> And so many eventually
can end up with a proposal

00:11:58.660 --> 00:12:00.640 align:middle line:84%
of a name that is very
different from yours.

00:12:00.640 --> 00:12:04.570 align:middle line:84%
Asking for a name is like really
trusting that the others can

00:12:04.570 --> 00:12:06.922 align:middle line:90%
see other parts of you.

00:12:06.922 --> 00:12:07.722 align:middle line:90%
(CHANTING) Mobula!

