00:12:23.760 --> 00:12:26.320 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:12:26.320 --> 00:12:48.130 align:middle line:90%


00:12:48.130 --> 00:12:50.800 align:middle line:84%
>> We have a complementary
currency system,

00:12:50.800 --> 00:12:54.510 align:middle line:84%
which is called credito,
that has been created since

00:12:54.510 --> 00:12:57.560 align:middle line:90%
the beginning of Damanhur.

00:12:57.560 --> 00:13:00.440 align:middle line:10%
>> It's called credito
because it's based on trust,

00:13:00.440 --> 00:13:03.380 align:middle line:10%
as if I give you credit.

00:13:03.380 --> 00:13:06.110 align:middle line:10%
And it's a beautiful currency.

00:13:06.110 --> 00:13:07.670 align:middle line:90%
It's also very artistic.

00:13:07.670 --> 00:13:13.750 align:middle line:84%
Each one of these coins
is beautifully created.

00:13:13.750 --> 00:13:16.870 align:middle line:84%
It's a currency that
was created years ago

00:13:16.870 --> 00:13:22.090 align:middle line:84%
in order to increase the
economic wealth of Damanhur,

00:13:22.090 --> 00:13:28.000 align:middle line:84%
allowing the citizen to spend
their euro or their lira

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:31.510 align:middle line:84%
at the time for the benefit
of the community buying homes

00:13:31.510 --> 00:13:36.790 align:middle line:84%
that they needed, land, and
creating this currency so

00:13:36.790 --> 00:13:39.610 align:middle line:84%
that it could circulate
among the citizens

00:13:39.610 --> 00:13:42.190 align:middle line:84%
so that new business
could be created

00:13:42.190 --> 00:13:47.220 align:middle line:84%
that could use this credit
or for the interior economy.

00:13:47.220 --> 00:13:51.440 align:middle line:84%
What happens is
when creating money

00:13:51.440 --> 00:13:53.900 align:middle line:84%
like this, which is an
alternative currency,

00:13:53.900 --> 00:14:02.240 align:middle line:84%
it has no connection with
big businesses, weapons, oil,

00:14:02.240 --> 00:14:04.820 align:middle line:90%
any kinds of--

00:14:04.820 --> 00:14:08.910 align:middle line:84%
all that regular
money is attached to.

00:14:08.910 --> 00:14:12.680 align:middle line:84%
It becomes a money
that is spiritually--

00:14:12.680 --> 00:14:15.190 align:middle line:90%


00:14:15.190 --> 00:14:16.450 align:middle line:90%
it has a spiritual value.

00:14:16.450 --> 00:14:18.700 align:middle line:90%
It has a spiritual meaning.

00:14:18.700 --> 00:14:21.520 align:middle line:84%
>> We want to really
use a spiritual coin,

00:14:21.520 --> 00:14:25.120 align:middle line:84%
a spiritual money in
order to share between us,

00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:28.750 align:middle line:84%
because Damanhur is
based on sharing.

00:14:28.750 --> 00:14:31.930 align:middle line:84%
It's based on spiritual
and ethical values

00:14:31.930 --> 00:14:33.470 align:middle line:90%
at the same time.

00:14:33.470 --> 00:14:35.800 align:middle line:84%
So everything has
to have a meaning.

00:14:35.800 --> 00:14:39.880 align:middle line:84%
Spirituality in Damanhur is
meant like giving meaning

00:14:39.880 --> 00:14:42.770 align:middle line:90%
every day, everything we do.

00:14:42.770 --> 00:14:50.980 align:middle line:84%
So we really marry together both
the spiritual idea of the life,

00:14:50.980 --> 00:14:54.010 align:middle line:84%
and also the practical things
that we do everyday life.

00:14:54.010 --> 00:14:57.260 align:middle line:90%


00:14:57.260 --> 00:15:00.200 align:middle line:84%
>> For us in Damanhur, the
connection to nature is very

00:15:00.200 --> 00:15:03.110 align:middle line:90%
important.

00:15:03.110 --> 00:15:06.840 align:middle line:84%
We have an understanding
of nature as an ecosystem.

00:15:06.840 --> 00:15:09.060 align:middle line:84%
Not only physical,
also spiritual.

00:15:09.060 --> 00:15:12.470 align:middle line:90%


00:15:12.470 --> 00:15:15.590 align:middle line:84%
We believe that the
divine is everywhere,

00:15:15.590 --> 00:15:19.010 align:middle line:84%
and that there are
different levels of being

00:15:19.010 --> 00:15:20.960 align:middle line:90%
conscious of being divine.

00:15:20.960 --> 00:15:23.900 align:middle line:84%
So the divine is also in
the smallest grain of sand.

00:15:23.900 --> 00:15:27.020 align:middle line:84%
And if we keep
looking and expanding,

00:15:27.020 --> 00:15:30.770 align:middle line:84%
we can meet and find
forces that extend

00:15:30.770 --> 00:15:32.930 align:middle line:90%
across time, across dimensions.

00:15:32.930 --> 00:15:36.550 align:middle line:84%
And those are the forces
that we call gods.

00:15:36.550 --> 00:15:39.340 align:middle line:84%
To create a future
of harmony, we also

00:15:39.340 --> 00:15:40.810 align:middle line:90%
really looked at our past.

00:15:40.810 --> 00:15:43.270 align:middle line:84%
And we saw that for
thousands of years,

00:15:43.270 --> 00:15:47.540 align:middle line:84%
people had been fighting
in name of God or gods.

00:15:47.540 --> 00:15:50.170 align:middle line:84%
And so we realized that
it was important to come

00:15:50.170 --> 00:15:51.910 align:middle line:84%
to a new understanding
of, what is

00:15:51.910 --> 00:15:55.840 align:middle line:84%
the relationship between the
human beings and the gods?

00:15:55.840 --> 00:15:57.580 align:middle line:84%
And we understand
that like there

00:15:57.580 --> 00:16:01.180 align:middle line:84%
is an ecosystem of the Earth
where everything is alive,

00:16:01.180 --> 00:16:04.540 align:middle line:84%
there is also a
spiritual ecosystem.

00:16:04.540 --> 00:16:08.920 align:middle line:84%
Everything has the same divine
origin and divine quality,

00:16:08.920 --> 00:16:11.590 align:middle line:84%
but not everybody is
aware of being a god.

00:16:11.590 --> 00:16:15.292 align:middle line:84%
So we humans have to
awaken to this reality.

00:16:15.292 --> 00:16:16.750 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
missions of Damanhur

00:16:16.750 --> 00:16:19.600 align:middle line:84%
is also that, to help
people and to activate

00:16:19.600 --> 00:16:23.430 align:middle line:84%
that divine presence
in themselves.

00:16:23.430 --> 00:16:26.880 align:middle line:10%
>> When you grow up in a system,
you sort of have to accept

00:16:26.880 --> 00:16:28.850 align:middle line:10%
the rules.

00:16:28.850 --> 00:16:31.360 align:middle line:84%
And that was also how I
was brought up in Denmark.

00:16:31.360 --> 00:16:35.130 align:middle line:84%
I always tried to fit in to the
structure of society in Denmark

00:16:35.130 --> 00:16:36.280 align:middle line:90%
and to the schools.

00:16:36.280 --> 00:16:38.160 align:middle line:84%
And it led to a
general frustration,

00:16:38.160 --> 00:16:41.700 align:middle line:84%
and it led to a sort of
seeking that then brought me

00:16:41.700 --> 00:16:43.890 align:middle line:90%
to Damanhur.

00:16:43.890 --> 00:16:47.670 align:middle line:84%
Living in the Sacred
Forest Temple of Damanhur

00:16:47.670 --> 00:16:51.360 align:middle line:84%
has been the huge
transformational process.

00:16:51.360 --> 00:16:54.450 align:middle line:90%
I lived there for eight years.

00:16:54.450 --> 00:16:55.380 align:middle line:90%
Seven, eight years.

00:16:55.380 --> 00:17:00.780 align:middle line:84%
And being integrated in the
way that Damanhur treats nature

00:17:00.780 --> 00:17:03.780 align:middle line:84%
and its contact with
nature, coming from a city,

00:17:03.780 --> 00:17:07.545 align:middle line:84%
coming from Copenhagen,
a big contrast that

00:17:07.545 --> 00:17:13.510 align:middle line:84%
has left a visible mark
on my heart, for sure.

00:17:13.510 --> 00:17:18.369 align:middle line:10%
>> I think it's the complicity
of the life force here

00:17:18.369 --> 00:17:22.930 align:middle line:10%
in the [ITALIAN] who helped me
to become the better version

00:17:22.930 --> 00:17:24.670 align:middle line:10%
of myself.

00:17:24.670 --> 00:17:28.060 align:middle line:84%
It is like living
in a spiritual gym.

00:17:28.060 --> 00:17:31.780 align:middle line:84%
Everything is moving, and
it moves things in you

00:17:31.780 --> 00:17:33.380 align:middle line:90%
at the same time.

00:17:33.380 --> 00:17:36.160 align:middle line:84%
So you're constantly
growing yourself

00:17:36.160 --> 00:17:37.750 align:middle line:90%
just by being in the woods.

00:17:37.750 --> 00:17:40.760 align:middle line:90%


00:17:40.760 --> 00:17:43.790 align:middle line:10%
>> This is also shown in the
rituals that we are doing,

00:17:43.790 --> 00:17:47.930 align:middle line:10%
ancient rituals that has been
practiced for many thousands

00:17:47.930 --> 00:17:50.960 align:middle line:10%
of years on the Earth like the
Equinox and the Solstice that

00:17:50.960 --> 00:17:55.740 align:middle line:10%
are all a celebration
of the pulse of nature.

00:17:55.740 --> 00:17:58.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Trees are so important,
because we consider them really

00:17:58.710 --> 00:18:00.150 align:middle line:90%
as a part of our soul.

00:18:00.150 --> 00:18:03.480 align:middle line:84%
The trees are the
antennas with the cosmos.

00:18:03.480 --> 00:18:07.410 align:middle line:84%
In our forest, there
miles and miles of mazes

00:18:07.410 --> 00:18:12.450 align:middle line:84%
built with colorful stones,
and they recreate energy lines,

00:18:12.450 --> 00:18:15.810 align:middle line:84%
the synchronic lines that
flow through the territory

00:18:15.810 --> 00:18:16.830 align:middle line:90%
of Damanhur.

00:18:16.830 --> 00:18:18.930 align:middle line:84%
Many, many people from
all around the world

00:18:18.930 --> 00:18:22.500 align:middle line:84%
come here to walk in our
mazes, to feel the energies,

00:18:22.500 --> 00:18:25.020 align:middle line:84%
to connect to the
trees, to celebrate

00:18:25.020 --> 00:18:29.190 align:middle line:84%
our union with everything,
with the cosmos through nature.

00:18:29.190 --> 00:18:31.620 align:middle line:84%
The stones have different
colors because colors,

00:18:31.620 --> 00:18:34.740 align:middle line:84%
they allow us also to stimulate
different areas of our brain

00:18:34.740 --> 00:18:35.770 align:middle line:90%
as we walk.

00:18:35.770 --> 00:18:38.890 align:middle line:84%
So it's a complete
involvement of all our senses.

00:18:38.890 --> 00:18:39.690 align:middle line:90%
We walk.

00:18:39.690 --> 00:18:40.950 align:middle line:90%
We use our concentration.

00:18:40.950 --> 00:18:42.795 align:middle line:90%
We stimulate our body, our mind.

00:18:42.795 --> 00:18:45.350 align:middle line:90%


00:18:45.350 --> 00:18:48.550 align:middle line:84%
>> The first question of
Damanhurian people was how we

00:18:48.550 --> 00:18:52.610 align:middle line:84%
can connect with the
plant world really.

00:18:52.610 --> 00:18:54.590 align:middle line:84%
Music of the plants
is a device that

00:18:54.590 --> 00:18:57.770 align:middle line:84%
helps us to hear the
sound of the plants.

00:18:57.770 --> 00:19:01.610 align:middle line:84%
And this sound is made
by the electrical signals

00:19:01.610 --> 00:19:02.750 align:middle line:90%
made by the plants.

00:19:02.750 --> 00:19:06.780 align:middle line:84%
We perceive the movement of
the lymph inside of the plants.

00:19:06.780 --> 00:19:09.350 align:middle line:84%
These perception
arrive to the device

00:19:09.350 --> 00:19:12.500 align:middle line:84%
and translate these
verses in music.

00:19:12.500 --> 00:19:17.460 align:middle line:90%
[SOFT MUSIC]

00:19:17.460 --> 00:19:42.756 align:middle line:90%


00:19:42.756 --> 00:19:47.716 align:middle line:90%
[DEEP MUSIC]

00:19:47.716 --> 00:19:49.220 align:middle line:90%


00:19:49.220 --> 00:19:51.870 align:middle line:84%
>> What is interesting is that
it translates the variation

00:19:51.870 --> 00:19:52.670 align:middle line:90%
of the plant.

00:19:52.670 --> 00:19:55.070 align:middle line:84%
This is why we have it in
the roof and in the leaves,

00:19:55.070 --> 00:19:57.890 align:middle line:84%
because that is how you can have
an interaction with the plant.

00:19:57.890 --> 00:20:00.560 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I also think
is the most exciting thing

00:20:00.560 --> 00:20:03.020 align:middle line:84%
with this device, is that
you can actually have

00:20:03.020 --> 00:20:04.340 align:middle line:90%
a conversation with a plant.

00:20:04.340 --> 00:20:07.490 align:middle line:84%
So this type of
interaction is for me

00:20:07.490 --> 00:20:09.320 align:middle line:84%
really a new field
of communication

00:20:09.320 --> 00:20:11.090 align:middle line:90%
with a different species.

00:20:11.090 --> 00:20:14.870 align:middle line:90%


00:20:14.870 --> 00:20:18.200 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea that this
type of interaction

00:20:18.200 --> 00:20:22.550 align:middle line:84%
would be so interesting also,
not only to have a contact

00:20:22.550 --> 00:20:25.410 align:middle line:84%
and actually understand
the plant life,

00:20:25.410 --> 00:20:28.160 align:middle line:84%
but I think that it's also
an interesting study of how

00:20:28.160 --> 00:20:30.260 align:middle line:84%
we also as human
beings can develop

00:20:30.260 --> 00:20:33.380 align:middle line:84%
our methods of communication
amongst each other.

00:20:33.380 --> 00:20:35.780 align:middle line:84%
Because I really think
that different species,

00:20:35.780 --> 00:20:38.480 align:middle line:84%
and especially the plants who
are interconnected underground

00:20:38.480 --> 00:20:39.920 align:middle line:90%
and are really like--

00:20:39.920 --> 00:20:41.632 align:middle line:84%
they have this
group consciousness,

00:20:41.632 --> 00:20:43.340 align:middle line:84%
and I really think
that that is something

00:20:43.340 --> 00:20:45.800 align:middle line:84%
that is needed in the
world today also when it

00:20:45.800 --> 00:20:47.850 align:middle line:90%
comes to human communication.

00:20:47.850 --> 00:20:50.732 align:middle line:84%
And so I think
that is personally

00:20:50.732 --> 00:20:52.940 align:middle line:84%
the most interesting part
of the music of the plants.

00:20:52.940 --> 00:20:56.290 align:middle line:90%


00:20:56.290 --> 00:20:59.800 align:middle line:84%
>> We find that most people
who visit Damanhur appreciate

00:20:59.800 --> 00:21:03.010 align:middle line:84%
the fact that here, they
find unity between everyday

00:21:03.010 --> 00:21:07.090 align:middle line:84%
and practical life, and
mysticism, spirituality,

00:21:07.090 --> 00:21:08.686 align:middle line:90%
and ritual.

00:21:08.686 --> 00:21:10.090 align:middle line:90%
[DRUMMING]

00:21:10.090 --> 00:21:13.100 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING ITALIAN]

00:21:13.100 --> 00:21:50.160 align:middle line:90%


00:21:50.160 --> 00:21:52.470 align:middle line:84%
>> There are different
ways to meditate.

00:21:52.470 --> 00:21:56.890 align:middle line:10%
Meditation means to be
not focused on a point,

00:21:56.890 --> 00:22:01.140 align:middle line:10%
but to be spread with your
consciousness in many points

00:22:01.140 --> 00:22:05.760 align:middle line:10%
at the same time, to be present
to yourself, into your body,

00:22:05.760 --> 00:22:07.260 align:middle line:10%
in the present.

00:22:07.260 --> 00:22:10.800 align:middle line:10%
Walking and movement,
you are expressing

00:22:10.800 --> 00:22:13.450 align:middle line:10%
all your different energies.

00:22:13.450 --> 00:22:17.310 align:middle line:10%
And if you follow
some specific lines,

00:22:17.310 --> 00:22:21.420 align:middle line:10%
you create an effect on
yourself because the shape

00:22:21.420 --> 00:22:22.822 align:middle line:10%
is very important.

00:22:22.822 --> 00:22:25.540 align:middle line:90%


00:22:25.540 --> 00:22:29.830 align:middle line:84%
>> What I find interesting
here is the different way we

00:22:29.830 --> 00:22:34.510 align:middle line:84%
perceive time, how each
knot of the spiral,

00:22:34.510 --> 00:22:38.470 align:middle line:84%
each new circuit of the
spiral becomes more in depth

00:22:38.470 --> 00:22:41.550 align:middle line:84%
into your own personal growth
and into your own personal

00:22:41.550 --> 00:22:42.350 align:middle line:90%
life.

00:22:42.350 --> 00:22:44.590 align:middle line:84%
So you come back to the
same point, I think,

00:22:44.590 --> 00:22:45.820 align:middle line:90%
in life many, many times.

00:22:45.820 --> 00:22:48.040 align:middle line:84%
But instead of seeing that
as linear or feeling that

00:22:48.040 --> 00:22:50.740 align:middle line:84%
you're stepping back, but really
fully then integrating the fact

00:22:50.740 --> 00:22:54.140 align:middle line:84%
that you're coming to the same
point but with new insights.

00:22:54.140 --> 00:22:58.450 align:middle line:84%
So you go deeper and deeper
into yourself and into life.

00:22:58.450 --> 00:23:00.320 align:middle line:84%
And this is where, I
think, that you grow.

00:23:00.320 --> 00:23:04.550 align:middle line:84%
This is where I feel that
I have grown the most.

00:23:04.550 --> 00:23:07.625 align:middle line:84%
My name is Celastrina,
and I've been here

00:23:07.625 --> 00:23:09.740 align:middle line:90%
in Damanhur for four years now.

00:23:09.740 --> 00:23:15.170 align:middle line:84%
And I came because I was
living in Stockholm in Sweden,

00:23:15.170 --> 00:23:17.580 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to change
my way of living.

00:23:17.580 --> 00:23:20.840 align:middle line:10%
And I was interested in
ecological ways of living

00:23:20.840 --> 00:23:23.520 align:middle line:10%
and especially in
community ways of living.

00:23:23.520 --> 00:23:26.000 align:middle line:84%
And I came to Damanhur
as the first community,

00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:29.840 align:middle line:84%
and I completely fell in
love with both the vision

00:23:29.840 --> 00:23:32.320 align:middle line:84%
and the practical work that
was done for this vision.

00:23:32.320 --> 00:23:35.005 align:middle line:84%
So I really liked the
concept of both dreaming,

00:23:35.005 --> 00:23:36.130 align:middle line:90%
but then also realizing it.

00:23:36.130 --> 00:23:40.920 align:middle line:90%
[WIND CHIMES]

00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:41.880 align:middle line:90%


00:23:41.880 --> 00:23:44.700 align:middle line:84%
>> We consider artistic
expression to be one

00:23:44.700 --> 00:23:47.640 align:middle line:84%
of the most direct ways to get
in touch with the divine within

00:23:47.640 --> 00:23:50.160 align:middle line:90%
each one of us.

00:23:50.160 --> 00:23:52.440 align:middle line:84%
The passion of
Damanhurians for the arts

00:23:52.440 --> 00:23:54.660 align:middle line:84%
can be seen not only
in Damanhur, but also

00:23:54.660 --> 00:23:57.420 align:middle line:84%
in the nearby
village of Vidracco.

00:23:57.420 --> 00:24:01.020 align:middle line:84%
The mayor and the administration
of Vidracco are Damanhurians,

00:24:01.020 --> 00:24:04.230 align:middle line:84%
and they encourage artists
from all over Italy

00:24:04.230 --> 00:24:06.480 align:middle line:84%
to come and share
the works of art

00:24:06.480 --> 00:24:07.845 align:middle line:90%
on the walls of every street.

00:24:07.845 --> 00:24:14.230 align:middle line:90%


00:24:14.230 --> 00:24:18.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Houses are painted with
flowers and animals very big

00:24:18.280 --> 00:24:22.030 align:middle line:84%
to help us understand that we
are not the only living beings,

00:24:22.030 --> 00:24:24.352 align:middle line:90%
but it's only about perspective.

00:24:24.352 --> 00:24:31.240 align:middle line:90%


00:24:31.240 --> 00:24:35.050 align:middle line:84%
>> It's this fantastic
artist community.

00:24:35.050 --> 00:24:38.380 align:middle line:84%
They really have implemented
art into every aspect

00:24:38.380 --> 00:24:41.440 align:middle line:84%
of their society, and they
made artists out of people

00:24:41.440 --> 00:24:42.880 align:middle line:90%
that were never artists before.

00:24:42.880 --> 00:24:45.820 align:middle line:90%


00:24:45.820 --> 00:24:49.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Many Damanhurians, they don't
have any formal or artistic

00:24:49.300 --> 00:24:52.190 align:middle line:84%
education before
joining the community.

